org.hibernate.type.descriptor.java.spi

Interface JavaTypeDescriptor<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    JavaTypeDescriptor<T>, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BasicJavaDescriptor<T>, EmbeddableJavaDescriptor<T>, EntityJavaDescriptor<T>, EnumJavaDescriptor<E>, IdentifiableJavaDescriptor<J>, ManagedJavaDescriptor<J>, MappedSuperclassJavaDescriptor<J>, NumericJavaDescriptor<T>, Primitive<J>, TemporalJavaDescriptor<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBasicJavaDescriptor, AbstractIdentifiableJavaDescriptor, AbstractManagedJavaDescriptor, AbstractNumericJavaDescriptor

    public interface JavaTypeDescriptor<T>
extends JavaTypeDescriptor<T>
    Descriptor for the Java side of a value mapping. We abstract from Class because domain types might be "virtual". Note however that we do require that all basic types be based on a real Java Class

      • unwrap

        <X> X unwrap(T value,
             Class<X> type,
             SharedSessionContractImplementor session)
        Unwrap an instance of our handled Java type into the requested type.

        As an example, if this is a JavaTypeDescriptor<Integer> and we are asked to unwrap the Integer value as a Long we would return something like Long.valueOf( value.longValue() ).

        Intended use is during PreparedStatement binding.

        Type Parameters:
        X - The conversion type.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to unwrap
        type - The type as which to unwrap
        session - The Session
        Returns:
        The unwrapped value.

      • wrap

        <X> T wrap(X value,
           SharedSessionContractImplementor session)
        Wrap a value as our handled Java type.

        Intended use is during ResultSet extraction.

        Type Parameters:
        X - The conversion type.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to wrap.
        session - The options
        Returns:
        The wrapped value.

      • toString

        default String toString(T value)
        To be honest we have no idea when this is useful. But older versions defined it, so in the interest of easier migrations we will keep it here. However, from our perspective it is the same as unwrap(T, java.lang.Class<X>, org.hibernate.engine.spi.SharedSessionContractImplementor) - so the default impl here does exactly that.
